09/26/22 
Soft Skills Recap Scrum Ceremonies

1. Product Backlog Groom meeting: 
PO is the one who is prioritizing the user stories to be worked on the next sprint & we are giving story points based on the complexity of this user story.

2. Daily Stand Up:
15-20 minutes on what you will be doing, what went well yesterday and if there's any obstacles.

3. Sprint Planning:
We are selecting user stories for the upcoming sprint. We can gather information and requirements by the time the next sprint comes along.

Sprint 1-4 weeks.

4. Sprint Review / Demo meeting
PO will review the increments on the user story (functionality) that we worked on.


5. Sprint Retrospective
-What went well
-What went bad
-What can we improve on

